<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">NOTICE OF APPEAL</TI>
<P><BOLD>THE APPELLANT/DEFENDANT 3395052 CANADA INC.</BOLD><FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P><BOLD>At the opening of the trial, counsel for the plaintiff indicated that the claim was being asserted only against Kutcher Dentistry Professional Corporation. See Reasons for Judgment at paragraph 12, last sentence.</BOLD></P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE> <BOLD>O/A KUTCHER DENTISTRY PROFESSIONAL CORPORATION APPEALS</BOLD> to the Court of Appeal for Ontario from the Judgment of the Honourable Madam Justice Chiappetta, dated May 25, 2018 (&ldquo;the Judgment&rdquo;), made at Toronto.</P>
<P><BOLD>THE APPELLANT ASKS</BOLD> that the Judgment be set aside and that
<P1>(a) the action be dismissed with costs of the action and of the appeal payable forthwith to the Appellant/Defendant in an amount to be fixed by this Honourable Court or following assessment, or</P1>
<P1>(b) in the alternative, the Judgment be varied as may be required by the findings of this Honourable Court on appeal with the costs of the appeal payable to the Appellant/Defendant and, to the extent warranted, the costs of the action varied accordingly; and</P1>
<P1>(c) granting leave to appeal the costs of the action awarded by the Learned Trial Judge and varying the costs award to the extent that this Honourable Court deems appropriate.</P1></P>
<P><BOLD>THE GROUNDS OF APPEAL</BOLD> are as follows:</P>
<P>1. The Judgment is wrong in fact and law and the Learned Trial Judge made one or more palpable and overriding error(s);</P>
<P>2. The Judgment is against the evidence tendered by the parties at trial;</P>
<P>3. The Learned Trial Judge erred in fact and in law in failing to properly analyze and apply the evidence and the submissions of the Appellant/Defendant and therefore made an incorrect assessment of credibility;</P>
<P>4. The Learned Trial Judge erred in law and in fact in assessing the evidence and submissions on the issue of mitigation;</P>
<P>5. The Learned Trial Judge erred in law and in fact in assessing the legal significance and effect of the Respondent's/Plaintiff's resignation on March 28, 2005, effective July 7, 2005, and of the offer of a new employment contract to her by 3395022 Canada Inc.;</P>
<P>6. The Learned Trial Judge erred in law and in fact in assessing and applying the evidence regarding the formal termination of the Respondent's/Plaintiff's employment, on October 1, 2011, to be effective December 31, 2011, by the 3395052 Canada Inc. and the offer of a new employment contract to her by the defendant Kutcher Dentistry Professional Corporation;</P>
<P>7. The Learned Trial Judge erred in the calculation of the Respondent's/Plaintiff's damages;</P>
<P>8. The Learned Trial Judge erred in awarding costs on the basis and in the amount she did following trial; and</P>
<P>9. Such further or other grounds as counsel shall advise and This Honourable Court permits.</P>
<P><BOLD>THE BASIS OF THE APPELLATE COURT'S JURISDICTION IS:</BOLD> s. 6(1) (b) of the <BOLD><EM>Courts of Justice Act</EM></BOLD>, R.S.O. 1990, c. C.43 as amended. The Judgment is a final order of the Superior Court of Justice for an amount in excess of $50,000.00, exclusive of costs, and leave to appeal the Judgment is not required.</P>
