<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="III"><UNDER>ENDORSEMENT</UNDER></TI>
<P>[1] The trial of this action took place before me over the course of less than two days. The plaintiff was awarded judgment in the amount of $69,091.12. The plaintiff now seeks her costs of the action in the amount of $26,198.65 which represents actual legal fees plus HST and disbursements.</P>
<P>[2] This was not a complicated case. There is no reason to award the plaintiff her actual costs incurred. Considering the principle of proportionality, the plaintiffs request is not consistent with what an unsuccessful party could reasonably expect to pay as costs for this simplified procedure matter. In my view, considering the factors enumerated at Rule 57.01(1) of the <EM>Rules of Civil Procedure</EM>, R.R.O. 1990, Reg. 194, it is a fair and reasonable exercise of my discretion under section 131 of the <EM>Courts of Justice Act</EM>. R.S.O. 1990 c. C.43 to fix costs of this action at $ 15,000 inclusive.</P>
<P>&ellip35; V.R. Chiappetta J.</P>
