<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">PART I&mdash;The Appeal</TI>
<P>1. The appellant appeals the May 25, 2018 and August 15, 2018 Judgment of Madam Justice V. R. Chiappetta delivered following a brief reserve after a 2 day trial.</P>
<P>2. The Learned Trial Judge granted the respondent judgment, awarded her damages in respect of 15 months' notice, deducting her modest acknowledged mitigation income, but not the statutory termination pay provided to her by the appellant nor income attributable to her, from selling / promoting Max International products, or other income earned, but not disclosed, during the notice period claimed. The damages awarded to the respondent are $69,091.12. The plaintiff was also awarded costs in the all-inclusive amount of $15,000.00.</P>
<P>3. The errors made by the Trial Judge are as follows:
<P1>(a) misconstruing and misinterpreting the facts and the law regarding the effect of the respondent's resignation on March 28, 2005;</P1>
<P1>(b) failing to properly consider and apply the clear evidence regarding the respondent's many credibility issues;</P1>
<P1>(c) not properly calculating the respondent's damages; and</P1>
<P1>(d) failing to properly consider and apply the facts and the evidence regarding the respondent's failure to take adequate or appropriate steps to mitigate her alleged damages.</P1></P>
<P>4. The appellant submits that these constitute palpable and overriding errors justifying this court's intervention.</P>
<P>5. The appellant appeals the issue of costs only to the extent that it seeks the costs of the appeal and the action if this appeal is successful.
<P1><BOLD>Judgment, dated May 25, 2018 and August 15, 2018, Appeal Book &amp; Compendium, Tab 2, pp. 4-5</BOLD></P1>
<P1><BOLD>Notice of Appeal, Appeal Book &amp; Compendium, Tab 1, pp. 1&ndash;3</BOLD></P1></P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">PART II&mdash;The Action and the Factual Background</TI>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Nature of the Action</EM></TI>
<P>6. This is a wrongful dismissal action, brought under the Simplified Procedure. In her Claim, the plaintiff sought: (a) a declaration that her employment was wrongfully dismissed: (b) payment of 15 months compensation in lieu of notice, less the statutory termination pay which was provided at the time of her termination<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>The Learned Trial Judge did not address the deduction of the termination pay in her Reasons for Judgment.</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE>; (c) pre and post-judgment interest; and (d) costs of the action.</P>
<P>7. Despite what is pled in paragraph 13 of the Statement of Claim <BOLD>[Appeal Book and Compendium, Tab 5, p. 21]</BOLD>, issued on December 3, 2014, 23 <TEXTFRAC>1/2</TEXTFRAC> months after the termination on December 20, 2012 <BOLD>[Exhibit 11&mdash;termination letter&mdash;Appeal Book &amp; Compendium, Tab 8&ndash;11, pp. 180],</BOLD> and the evidence led in the plaintiff's testimony in chief of alleged threats, plaintiff's counsel admitted, at the close of the plaintiff's case in chief, that there was no plea of duress nor was the plaintiff alleging or relying on any assertion of duress in this action.
