<BLOCK3><TI>The Employment Relationship and the Chronological Sequence</TI>
<P>10. The plaintiff commenced working for Dr. Victor Kutcher, (&ldquo;Dr. Kutcher&rdquo;) a periodontist practicing in Stoney Creek in the province of Ontario, in September 1993. At the time, Dr. Kutcher was practicing as an unincorporated sole practitioner.</P>
<P>11. In 1997 3395022 Canada Inc. <BOLD>(&ldquo;3395022&rdquo;)</BOLD> was incorporated as a hygiene company. Throughout its existence it always employed all of and only the hygienists employed in the dental practice. The plaintiff was paid by 3395022 from the time of its establishment until December 31, 2011. Neither Dr. Kutcher nor any of the dental assistants or administrative staff were ever compensated through 3395022. 3395022 was not owned, either directly or beneficially, by Dr. Kutcher.
