<P>27. Dr. Kutcher denied in his evidence that he (a) ever told the plaintiff, or other hygienists, they should not worry about signing the contracts he offered them; (b) or that <EM>&ldquo;if, you don't sign the contract, your gone&rdquo;</EM> and (c) that he put time limits on their responding to the contracts he offered them. The Trial Judge indicated that <EM>&ldquo;the plaintiff had to sign the contract prior to the end of the 2011 fiscal year end in order to continue employment.&rdquo;</EM> <BOLD>[Reasons, para 13&mdash;Appeal Book and Compendium, Tab 3, pp. 8-9]</BOLD>
